radiographic_examinations.findings: Periportal edema and pericholystic edema; gallbladder appears unremarkable. The lung bases, spleen, bilateral kidneys, bilateral adrenal glands, and pancreas all appear unremarkable. No bowel obstruction or bowel wall thickening is seen. The appendix is visualized with appendicoliths and no definite periappendiceal stranding; the diameter of the appendix is top normal at 6 mm. Trace, physiologic free fluid is seen in the pelvis; uterus and adnexa appear unremarkable.
